The energy industry of Dnipropetrovsk has started a unique program to save... nests of storks
In the old days, to bring to the court of storks, the villagers on a high pole installed a wheel from the cart, and a heavy nest was well kept on it.
Such special supports have not been put for a long time, so storks have chosen poles of power lines - intertwined branches are based on wires, so the aistic house is reliable.
Grandmother Anya, near whose house in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district for twenty years lives the eastern family, began to notice how the nest settles, despite all the efforts of its inhabitants.
Birds put on top of new twigs, and the bottom layer has already sat between the wires, is about to collapse.
Of course, I feel sorry for the family of storks, who every year nested at the yard, bred and fed over the summer three or four chicks, but without light do not want to remain.
As soon as the birds flew to the warm lands, Grandma Anya called the Tsarichansky RES, which owns the support.
I didn't expect to react so quickly.
When our specialists came to Ivanovka, they were surprised that the nest is still holding, - said Sergei Berezovsky, technical director of DTEK Dniproblanergo.
On the wires, which were, in fact, already inside the nest, weighing 150 - 200 kilograms, began corrosion.
At any moment the birds could have died from electric discharge.
And the locals risked being left without light because of the damage to the wires.
Therefore, linear installers have started an operation to save the nest, and not for the first time in our practice.
Ornithologists from the Dnipropetrovsk National University helped, who developed a scheme to move the nest.
They also conducted trainings for the employees of the district networks.
The well-known Dnipropetrovsk ornithologist Alexander Ponomarenko advised energy engineers at all stages of nest reconstruction.
To begin with, it was estimated that more than 50 "apartments" are in a state of emergency in the region.
Special metal platforms resembling a funnel were welded for their reconstruction.
The base was woven with willy branches, and then moved there the old nest.
According to connoisseurs, it is enough to lay the old branches as a basis for the birds to know the nest and return to it.
Even then the storks will finish their own home.
A month ago, the first nest was reconstructed in the village of Peschanka in the Novomoskovsky district.
Next to the electric pole put a new reinforced concrete pole and placed on it a platform with an old, already inhabited nest.
The whole operation cost the energy industry nine thousand hryvnias.
And the other day the same housewarming took place in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district on the backyard of Ani's grandmother.
Here the platform was fixed in the same place, only raised above the wires.
Ornithologists are sure that cautious, conservative birds will not even notice in the spring that their "apartment" has undergone an overhaul.
By the end of the year, the same reconstruction awaits four more nests in the Pokrovsk and Tsarichan districts of Dnipropetrovsk.
By the way, while some save rare birds, others ruthlessly kill them.
The other day the whole region flew around the sad news - in the village of Ust-Kamenka Apostolovsky district, on the day of the opening of the hunt for pheasants, poachers for fun shot the swan family, living on a local pond.
Noble birds were not afraid of people - the locals fed them and did not offend them.
When the villagers, hearing gunshots, ran to the pond, four handsome swans were already lying on the water dead.
Now the officers of the Apostolovsky district police department are investigating who shot the birds listed in the Red Book.
