FAA: "Air passengers can now use gadgets on planes (but not to call from a mobile phone)"
Air passengers will be able to use their electronic devices throughout the flight to read, work, play games, watch movies and listen to music, but not talk on mobile phones, according to a long-awaited new guidelines released Thursday by the Federal Aviation Administration.
But passengers should not expect changes to happen immediately.
How quickly such a change is implemented will vary depending on the airline, FAA Administrator Michael Huerta said at a news conference.
Airlines will have to show the FAA how their aircraft meet the new guidelines and that they are updating their flight crew training manuals and device styling rules to comply with the new guidelines.
