In Singapore, about 70% of the things laid in 200 pawnshops of the city-state are gold products.
People say, "The price of gold looks good, let's lay down grandma's gold chain and get it back next month."
In Thailand, easyMoney, the largest pawnshop operator, has seen a 20% increase in the number of customers using its branches in recent months.
The growth in the pawnshop business is such that ValueMax, a branch operator in Bendemir and 15 others similar in Singapore, plans to expand not only in neighboring Malaysia, where it has four stores, but also outside Asia too, said Yah Lee Ching, CEO of ValueMax.
